I want you.

00:05:49.170 --> 00:05:51.902
You want me as well, don't you?

00:05:51.902 --> 00:05:54.020
-Bianca, please
don't do this to me.

00:05:54.020 --> 00:05:55.318
Bianca, stop it!

00:05:55.318 --> 00:05:56.722
Stop it!

00:05:56.722 --> 00:05:59.023
For crying out loud, are you
trying to drive me insane?

00:06:01.542 --> 00:06:03.630
Bianca, you can only
push a bloke so far.

00:06:03.630 --> 00:06:05.540
Do you know what I mean?

00:06:05.540 --> 00:06:06.380
-Well, why?

00:06:06.380 --> 00:06:07.220
What have I done?

00:06:07.220 --> 00:06:09.392
-You know what you did.

00:06:09.392 --> 00:06:10.374
-Well, damn, why not?

00:06:10.374 --> 00:06:12.829
I mean, what's your problem?

00:06:12.829 --> 00:06:14.302
-I'm your father, all right?

00:06:21.190 --> 00:06:22.208
-No, you ain't.

00:06:25.624 --> 00:06:27.576
You can't be.

00:06:27.576 --> 00:06:30.016
-I can be.

00:06:30.016 --> 00:06:31.480
And I am.

00:06:35.384 --> 00:06:38.312
I'm sorry.

00:06:38.312 --> 00:06:40.699
I'm-- I'm really, really sorry.

00:06:44.611 --> 00:06:48.034
You shouldn't have
found out like this.

00:06:48.034 --> 00:06:49.990
Yeah.

00:06:49.990 --> 00:06:52.924
I'm-- Come on.

00:06:52.924 --> 00:06:54.391
-Don't.

00:06:54.391 --> 00:06:58.320
Don't touch me.

00:06:58.320 --> 00:07:01.070
Just leave me alone.

00:07:01.070 --> 00:07:03.070
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:07:03.070 --> 00:07:05.013
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:07:05.013 --> 00:07:07.744
[APPLAUSE]

00:07:07.744 --> 00:07:09.410
JOHN YORKE: I'm not
sure you're supposed

00:07:09.410 --> 00:07:12.840
to laugh quite that much.

00:07:12.840 --> 00:07:13.730
It's fine.

00:07:13.730 --> 00:07:14.730
It's rather dated.

00:07:14.730 --> 00:07:16.050
And it is what it is.

00:07:16.050 --> 00:07:19.270
But what I want to use it
to, say, illustrate hopefully

00:07:19.270 --> 00:07:22.290
a deeper point.

00:07:22.290 --> 00:07:24.320
For years, I set up the
BBC Writer's Academy.

00:07:24.320 --> 00:07:28.570
And my job has been to
teach people storytelling.

00:07:28.570 --> 00:07:30.850
And I developed this
ridiculously shorthand,

00:07:30.850 --> 00:07:33.690
ridiculously simplistic
way of trying

00:07:33.690 --> 00:07:36.750
to analyze how a story
works if you get stuck.

00:07:36.750 --> 00:07:39.630
And I came up with a system,
which if you ask 10 questions

00:07:39.630 --> 00:07:42.420
and you could answer them all,
probably that will give you

00:07:42.420 --> 00:07:43.590
a story shape.

00:07:43.590 --> 00:07:46.030
And as those 10 were
questions, very quickly,

00:07:46.030 --> 00:07:47.400
whose story is it?

00:07:47.400 --> 00:07:49.630
What's the flaw in
their character?

00:07:49.630 --> 00:07:51.470
What's the inciting incident?

00:07:51.470 --> 00:07:52.730
What do they want?

00:07:52.730 --> 00:07:55.220
What obstacles are in their way?

00:07:55.220 --> 00:07:56.430
What's at stake?

00:07:56.430 --> 00:07:58.220
Why should we care?

00:07:58.220 --> 00:07:59.820
What do they learn?

00:07:59.820 --> 00:08:02.135
How and why do they change?

00:08:02.135 --> 00:08:03.890
And how does it end?

00:08:03.890 --> 00:08:06.930
OK, so very simple,
again, simplistic

00:08:06.930 --> 00:08:09.940
for obvious reasons-- brevity.

00:08:09.940 --> 00:08:12.471
But you take those 10 questions.

00:08:12.471 --> 00:08:14.470
Let's have a look at that
scene we've just seen.

00:08:14.470 --> 00:08:16.870
Because it applies
to whole stories.

00:08:16.870 --> 00:08:18.940
it applies to
episodes of stories.

00:08:18.940 --> 00:08:21.690
But it also applies
to scenes themselves,

00:08:21.690 --> 00:08:23.800
because dramatic
structure is fractal.

00:08:23.800 --> 00:08:28.290
So it's the same units
enlarged time and time again.

00:08:28.290 --> 00:08:31.300
So if we take David's story,
and again simplistic answers,

00:08:31.300 --> 00:08:32.049
who's story is it?

00:08:32.049 --> 00:08:33.500
Well, it's David's, obviously.

00:08:33.500 --> 00:08:35.330
What's his flaw?

00:08:35.330 --> 00:08:37.809
Well, he has a knowledge
the he hasn't imparted,

00:08:37.809 --> 00:08:40.070
which is I'm your
father, obviously.

00:08:40.070 --> 00:08:43.600
This was before "Star Wars," I'd
like to make this quite clear.

00:08:43.600 --> 00:08:45.080
What's the inciting incident?

00:08:45.080 --> 00:08:49.080
What's the event that sparks
off the problem, the catalyst?

00:08:49.080 --> 00:08:50.250
Bianca tries to kiss him.

00:08:50.250 --> 00:08:51.270
What does he want?

00:08:51.270 --> 00:08:55.000
Well, he wants to
stop her kissing him.

00:08:55.000 --> 00:08:56.730
Sort of.

00:08:56.730 --> 00:08:58.700
What obstacles are in his way?

00:08:58.700 --> 00:09:01.420
Well, obviously, Bianca.

00:09:01.420 --> 00:09:03.560
It's very simple.

00:09:03.560 --> 00:09:05.120
And then we move
on, what's at stake?

00:09:05.120 --> 00:09:07.220
Well, his mental state,
I think we can probably

00:09:07.220 --> 00:09:11.630
say, a few laws perhaps as well.

00:09:11.630 --> 00:09:13.210
Why should we care?

00:09:13.210 --> 00:09:17.080
Well, hopefully we like
the character-- not like,

00:09:17.080 --> 00:09:19.210
but there's something about
him that we care about.

00:09:19.210 --> 00:09:19.910
He's vulnerable.

00:09:19.910 --> 00:09:21.430
We empathize with him.

00:09:21.430 --> 00:09:22.856
What does he learn?

00:09:22.856 --> 00:09:24.590
He learns to tell the truth.

00:09:24.590 --> 00:09:25.970
How and why?

00:09:25.970 --> 00:09:28.690
Bianca pushes him to
the point of no return,

00:09:28.690 --> 00:09:30.817
sexual arousal, et cetera.

00:09:30.817 --> 00:09:32.400
Because at some
level, clearly there's

00:09:32.400 --> 00:09:35.070
something going on that he's
very uncomfortable with.

00:09:35.070 --> 00:09:36.870
How does it end?

00:09:36.870 --> 00:09:38.900
The knowledge is imparted.

00:09:38.900 --> 00:09:41.080
OK, so very
simplistic, but it will

00:09:41.080 --> 00:09:43.160
do as a kind of rule of thumb.

00:09:43.160 --> 00:09:45.980
Let's have a look at Bianca
and what Bianca does.

00:09:45.980 --> 00:09:48.227
Because what if
it's Bianca's story?

00:09:48.227 --> 00:09:49.060
And what do you get?

00:09:49.060 --> 00:09:49.810
Whose story is it?

00:09:49.810 --> 00:09:51.750
Well, obviously, it's Bianca's.

00:09:51.750 --> 00:09:52.736
What's her flaw?

00:09:52.736 --> 00:09:54.735
Well, it's a lack of
knowledge of the situation.

00:09:54.735 --> 00:09:56.460
It's her innocence.

00:09:56.460 --> 00:09:59.220
What's the inciting incident?

00:09:59.220 --> 00:10:01.200
He rejects her.

00:10:01.200 --> 00:10:03.230
She wants to sleep with him.

00:10:03.230 --> 00:10:04.810
What obstacles are in their way?

00:10:04.810 --> 00:10:08.135
Well, David and
David's behavior.

00:10:08.135 --> 00:10:09.590
What's at stake?

00:10:09.590 --> 00:10:10.980
Her mental state.

00:10:10.980 --> 00:10:12.300
Why should we care?

00:10:12.300 --> 00:10:14.270
Arguably, she's vulnerable.

00:10:14.270 --> 00:10:16.145
Two, what does she learn?

00:10:16.145 --> 00:10:19.680
She's going to learn
to deny the truth.

00:10:19.680 --> 00:10:20.270
How and why?

00:10:20.270 --> 00:10:22.640
David pushes her to
the point of no return.

00:10:22.640 --> 00:10:24.710
How does it end?

00:10:24.710 --> 00:10:26.300
Truth rejected-- "No you ain't.

00:10:26.300 --> 00:10:28.190
Get away from me."

00:10:28.190 --> 00:10:31.500
OK, so again, very
simple, I've brought it

00:10:31.500 --> 00:10:33.380
right down to absolute basics.

00:10:33.380 --> 00:10:37.020
But clearly, there's
a pattern going on.

00:10:37.020 --> 00:10:39.220
And what this pattern,
I think, introduces to,

00:10:39.220 --> 00:10:42.360
which is really the heart of
the physics and the physics

00:10:42.360 --> 00:10:44.290
that underpin story
I want to talk today,

00:10:44.290 --> 00:10:48.180
is about this, this
extraordinary universe

00:10:48.180 --> 00:10:50.600
of opposites.

